posts.title: Rand Paul, other senators are Big Mad about FEMA blowing its wad on assisting foreigners invade our southern border, rather than helping Hurricane victim citizens.   I propose a Bill that dissolves FEMA and instead takes its funding, divides evenly among states and gives to governors for emergencies
posts.content:
> We're giving it back to you, the American people

From Rand Paul's drip marketing email

Image

Dear Friend,

You can find my latest update below!

Dr. Rand Paul Calls Out Biden Admin for Using FEMA to Respond to Border, Weakening Storm Response Readiness

Recently, as Ranking Member of the Senate Homeland Security and Governmental Affairs Committee, I, along with Senators James Lankford (R-OK), Ron Johnson (R-WI), Josh Hawley (R-MO), and Roger Marshall (R-KS), sent a letter to President Joe Biden calling out the Administration’s reliance on the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to address the border crisis which has diminished FEMA’s readiness for disaster relief, including hurricane response.

ImageAs we wrote in the letter, FEMA’s continued entanglement in DHS’s efforts to respond to the border crisis could impact its readiness and emergency response mission. Rather than ensuring FEMA is ready to respond to hurricanes and other emergencies, FEMA has been pulled into a border crisis mission. FEMA’s mission is ‘helping people before, during, and after disasters,’ not helping DHS clean up the impact of the Biden Administration’s reckless border policies. We are very concerned that FEMA’s role at the border has impacted its readiness and preparation efforts for Hurricane Helene and its response efforts.

You can read more about our efforts HERE and HERE, and read the full letter to President Biden HERE.

Dr. Rand Paul to Host Veteran Constituent Services Fair in Winchester

Veterans and other community members are invited to attend my Veteran Constituent Services Fair on Friday, October 25, from 4:00pm-6:00pm ET at Anna’s House in Winchester. Members of my state team and our Veterans Administration partners will join me to answer questions, offer resources and assist any Kentuckian needing assistance with a federal agency. Community members are encouraged to attend to learn about the services my state team provides.

As your representative in the United States Senate, I am wholly committed to ensuring every Kentucky Veteran receives the support they were promised.

For more information and to RSVP, please contact my State Office at 270-782-8303.

Dr. Rand Paul Visits Berry Global in Bowling Green

Proposal

A bill that dissolves FEMA and returns the ledger of what the fed gov has given; and says whatever they gave this year, you now give to the federation of US state governors or whatever the heck its called.

And then you divide among states (and commonwealths, and P.R.), and give to their governors.

The governors are to use these funds for emergencies. And it follows that the gov is going to let his state, his constituents decide on what is an emergency and what is not. IF they abuse it, well then the people of that state will have their head.

Nothing stopping governors from one state helping the gov of another.

There is another rule. They get the same amount every year. They don't have to spend it all to get it again. They can accumulate, but the amount they in their account (their account balance) is posted on a live map of the states that everyone can see.

In a crowdsourcy kind of way, the constituents of a country can perennially vote on what's an emergency in their state but they can also vote on whether their money for the state should go to another state that needs their help, and how much.

In this way this voting crowdsourcy kind of app acts as a state referendum or 4th branch of gov at the state executive level
